Source: mesa
Section: graphics
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Marcelo E. Magallon <mmagallo@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.5.8
Build-Depends: libggi2-dev [alpha arm hppa i386 ia64 m68k mips mipsel powerpc s390 sparc], libglide2-dev [i386], lesstif2-dev, xlibs-dev, automake, libtool, autoconf, g++ (>= 2:3.2), grep-dctrl

Package: mesag3
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, libglu1-mesa
Conflicts: mesag3-glide, mesag3-glide2, mesag3+ggi, libgl1, nvidia-glx
Provides: libgl1
Replaces: libgl1
Description: A 3-D graphics library which implements the OpenGL API
 Mesa is a 3-D graphics library with an API which is very similar to
 that of OpenGL.  To the extent that Mesa utilizes the OpenGL command
 syntax or state machine, it is being used with authorization from
 Silicon Graphics, Inc.  However, the author makes no claim that Mesa
 is in any way a compatible replacement for OpenGL or associated with
 Silicon Graphics, Inc.

Package: mesag-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: mesag3 (= ${Source-Version}), libc6-dev, xlibs-dev, mesa-common-dev (= ${Source-Version})
Provides: libgl-dev, mesag3-widgets, mesag-widgets-dev
Conflicts: mesa-dev, libgl-dev, mesag3 (<< 3.1-1), nvidia-glx-dev
Replaces: libgl-dev
Description: Development library for Mesa
 Includes headers and static libraries for compiling programs with mesa.

Package: libglu1-mesa
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Provides: libglu1
Conflicts: mesag3 (<< 5.0.0-1), xlibmesa3, libglu1
Replaces: libglu1
Description: The OpenGL utility library, libGLU
 The OpenGL utility library (GLU) offers simple interfaces for building
 mipmaps; checking for the presence of extensions in the OpenGL (or
 other libraries which follow the same conventions for advertising
 extensions); drawing piecewise linear curves, NURBS, quadrics and other
 primitives (including, but not limited to, teapots); tesselating
 surfaces; setting up projection matrices and unprojecting screen
 coordinates to world coordinates.

Package: libglu1-mesa-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, libglu1-mesa (= ${Source-Version})
Provides: libglu-dev
Conflicts: mesag-dev (<< 5.0.0-1), mesa-glide2-dev (<< 5.0.0-1), mesag3+ggi-dev (<< 5.0.0-1), xlibmesa-dev
Replaces: libglu-dev
Description: The OpenGL utility library development environment
 Includes headers and static libraries for compiling programs with GLU.

