Package: mesa-common-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: all
Depends: mesag-dev (>> 5) | mesag-glide2-dev (>> 5) | mesag3+ggi-dev (>> 5), libglu1-mesa-dev
Description: Developer documentation for Mesa
 This package includes the specifications for the Mesa-specific OpenGL
 extensions, the complete set of release release notes and the
 development header files common to all Mesa packages.

Package: libosmesa4
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: mesag3 (= ${Source-Version})
Conflicts: xlibosmesa3
Replaces: xlibosmesa3
Provides: xlibosmesa3
Description: Mesa Off-screen rendering extension
 OSmesa is a Mesa extension that allows programs to render to an
 off-screen buffer using the OpenGL API without having to create a
 rendering context on a X Server.  It uses a pure software renderer.

Package: libosmesa4-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: libosmesa4 (= ${Source-Version}), mesag-dev (= ${Source-Version})
Conflicts: xlibosmesa-dev
Replaces: xlibosmesa-dev
Provides: xlibosmesa-dev
Description: Mesa Off-screen rendering extension -- development support files
 This package contains all the headers and support files required for
 developing programs that use the off-screen rendering extension of
 Mesa.  For more information on OSmesa see the libosmesa4 package.
